<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/fd6fe616cf9b67cb6e934b3f7f6fc9be.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 6 and c = 12. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>10.4</li><li>30.0</li><li>60.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12}^{{2}}={6}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{144}={36}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{144}-{36}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{108}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{108}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{10.392304845413}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{10.4}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{6}}{{12}}\right)}}}\approx{30}\approx{30}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{6}}{{12}}\right)}}}\approx{60}\approx{60}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

